parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to reprogram the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission does not respond properly to the computer
the parking brakes get mixed up
the gear control goes into reverse when put in drive
the parking brake default light and transmission default light are on
the vehicle jumps into reverse gear
and the transmission defaults while in drive
causing the vehicle to not accelerate or move properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates abnormally
the vehicle accelerates backward
and the vehicle will not move forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission noise and clunking can indicate a faulty transmission, leading to premature wear and potential failure.
symptoms: Transmission noise when shifting from 3rd to 4th gear
clunking noise when downshifting from 3rd to 2nd gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shifter problems can cause the vehicle to become immobilized, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Shifter becomes stuck
will not come out of park without great force
breaks the plastic piece necessary to change gears
resulting in complete immobility of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brakes locking up while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The rear brakes lock up
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the vehicle may skid or slide
the brakes may fail to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage
the parking brake engages unintentionally
the vehicle moves unexpectedly
the brake warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic ABS brake module can cause unintended application of the parking brake, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake engages unintentionally
the brake warning light illuminates
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the vehicle may skid or slide.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic parking brake module can cause the parking brake to engage unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or even fires.
symptoms: The parking brake engages while driving
the rear brakes lock and start to smoke
the vehicle suddenly stops or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off while driving
the vehicle will not accelerate
the vehicle operates normally for 3-4 weeks and then cuts off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of various sensors and components can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The restricted performance light illuminates
the sunvisor breaks
the coolant pump outlet hose needs to be replaced
the electrically operated front seat runner and motor assembly fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause the vehicle to come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to damage to the vehicle and other property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or comes to a complete stop while driving
the vehicle jerks or hesitates while accelerating
the engine knocks or makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power or RPMs while driving.
